    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Samsung Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fibrin sealant has been studied to reduce post-thyroidectomy drain and hospital stay as well.
      However, no strong evidence from well-designed clinical trials is available. Harmonic scalpel
      is a ultrasonic vibrating scissors which makes it easy to cut and coagulate the tissues, thus
      reducing op time and postoperative drain, which is important to minimize hospital stay. The
      investigators hypothesized that fibrin sealant combined with harmonic scalpel-assisted
      procedure could guarantee no-drain postoperative care in total thyroidectomy with anterior
      compartment neck dissection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
